page.title: 05SHOPS AND PUBS,WITHERNSEA
page.content: Most shops are concentrated along the main street and present a diversity of type.There are 2 main foodstores, branches of large concerns.Both open for late-night shopping and sell wine, spirits and tobacco.There is a branch of Woolworths and a large chemists, formerly owned by Boots but now in the hands of a regional company.There are 5 building societies,although most are linked to estate agents,and 3 banks, Midland,National Westminster and T.S.B. Most shops have small frontages and several are speciality shops run by local people and catering for the tourist trade.The gas and electricity boards have showrooms. There are a large number of public houses,although they tend to be small and traditional,catering only for basic needs with a lack of sophistication.Most are tied houses.
